In a mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs until well mixed. Combine dry ingredients; add to butter mixture alternately with water and buttermilk. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 375 degrees F for 5-7 minutes or until done. Cool completely. In a small mixing bowl, beat filling ingredients until fluffy. Spread filling on half of the cookies, then top with remaining cookies.